postcontent:
The Rocky Mountain Elk Foundation and Browning/Winchester created a very limited quantity of Winchester Teddy Roosevelt 1895 Commemorative Rifle.  The rifle honors and commemorates the 100th anniversary of Theodore Roosevelt's African Safari of 1909. The rifle is patterned after the gun he loved, the Winchester Model 1895. 

This is a Model 1895 Safari Centennial High Grade rifle. It's chambered in the famous .405 Winchester caliber. The deal is supplied with a complete collector's package, including a deluxe canvas and leather double gun hard case, full color box sleeve, special edition hang tag, special owner's manual and a hardbound copy of President Roosevelt's famous book "African Game Trails" edited by Peter Capstick. 

The High Grade rifle has fancy Grade II/III walnut with fine cut checkering on the forearm and butt stock. The silver nitride receiver features deep engraving of many African big game animals plus extensive gold-toned embellishments on the lever.

The rifle includes a gold Theodore Roosevelt's signature on the receiver; a genuine ivory medallion embedded in the stock, a buckhorn rear sight and a marble gold bead front sight.

I will take partial trades so please include what item you have and all applicable info (condition, etc.) along with the cash you're willing to add and I'll consider it with the others. 

When you fire this gun it's immediately obvious you're not behind a normal AR-15 in 5.56. It's got a kick to let you know there's a 50 cal bullet headed downrange. It is manageable though and is similar to shooting an auto 20g shotgun or maybe even lighter than that. This one was test fired by the builder and is an absolute blast to shoot. It runs like a typewriter and is incredibly reliable. 

Several of these rifles have been sent to our troops in the middle east to test at Check-Points. If a vehicle refuses to stop they fire one of these giant bullets from their modified AR to instantly seize the motor and stop the vehicle.

50 Cals are on the chopping block for gun control ban legislation so they may not be available much longer.

title: For Sale:  Thompson Center Renegade 50 cal. Flintlock
postcontent:
I have a used Thompson Center Renegade 50 cal. Flintlock for sale. The Renegade is the no frills, no brass (grey steel furniture) version of the T/C Hawken, made in the 80s and 90s. The gun is 43" long and has a 27" barrel with 1:48 twist. I am selling it because I found an unshot one on GunBroker that had spent a lot of years in a closet, and its a good compact gun for deer hunting.

This is not a new or beautiful gun, and some of the miles show, but it shoots fine. It is a hunter vs. a show it off gun! There is minor surface rust on the outside of the barrel. I was planning to naturally brown it, but I have no time free to do it!

I replaced the frizzen about a month ago, and had the old man at Dixons check the lock assembly. I shot it last weekend to make sure I could still hit something before second season. It shoots well with a .015 lubed patch for ball.

I have shot 175 gr. ball (65 gr. FFg), Hornady 240 gr. PA conicals (80 gr. FFg), and Hornady 285 gr. Plains Bullets (85 gr. FFg) through it. At 75 yds. They all will produce a 4" grouping with those powder loads (with a steady eye).. 

It will also shoot FFFg, if you back off the volume by 15%, and though T/C says you can shoot sabots in the Hawken and Renegade, I dont like the performance!

I will include for the Buyer a dozen 175 gr. ball and a stack of lubed and unlubed patches, and a dozen of the PA conicals. There is also an extra flint and leather and a cleaning jag in a flat tin to store it all. All you need is the powder and prime!

I can meet anywhere within 20 miles of the I-81/I-83 intersection.

If you email, leave a number, and I will call you back as soon as I can. Email is on the Droid, so it will be soon after!

title: For Sale:  Everyone chill out, who pays these prices??? It's a joke.
postcontent: Seriously, if you pay over 300 for 1,000 rounds of 7.62x39 or over 500/600 for a 1,000 rounds of .223/5.56 YOU'RE A FUCKING PARANOID MORON. Every ammo website has been constantly putting more ammo on their sites multiple times a day for half the price of what people try to charge on here for stuff that has been sitting in their closet loosely packed for years. Talked to Promag company, they're working 24/7 with two shifts of people to pump out as many mags as they can. All these shooting supply stores have had their ammo stocked up for years and years and had thousands of pmags in the back, then everyone freaks out and buys every single thing the stores have, then these ammo and mag companies have to restock THE WHOLE COUNTRY at once in just a few days, so people freak and think its gone for good just bc the stores can't restock immediately. Congress is out for Christmas, even if every person in Congress agreed we should pass laws banning bulk ammo and high cap mags, it would take over a month just to pass it. Ammo companies and mag companies will fill our orders in that time (I promise you, they want to fill our orders just as bad as we want it). What people forget is we have tons of reps in congress which do not support gun control laws. Lastly, why the hell do people think the assault weapons are going anywhere? Obama could never pass that because pressure from all the huge gun manufactures and NRA. SURE, he might pass a ban on 30 round mags and certain collapsable stocks, but the guns themselves aren't going anywhere. Sources- Brother works for NRA, Grandfather owns an outdoors store.

title: For Sale:  Lyman 50 cal. Great Plains Flintlock Rifle
postcontent:
I have a used 50 cal. Lyman Great Plains Rifle for sale. I would rate it's condition at 85-90%. The bore is shiny and edges of the lands sharp. It has a 32-1/2" barrel with a 1:60 twist, and an overall length of 49-1/2". It has a double set trigger. This rifle is the closest reproduction of the true Hawken Bros. rifle of St. Louis fame. It is just too much rifle for my means, and only gets shot once or twice a year at a friends house with the Blackpowder locals! I prefer a shorter rifle, because of the laurels and thickets I hunt in,and I have an unfired T/C Renegade due in by UPS Monday! And hopefully this will be in someones hands for the second season!

I put new wedges in a couple of weeks ago. I shot it last weekend, and it is ready to go. The rifle is designed for, and shoots FFFg powder, which is a bit faster ignition, and of which I will include a half a can of with the rifle. I have shot 175 gr. round ball with a .018 lubed patch, 240 gr. PA conicals, and the true deerslayer for a Lyman GPR or other 50 cal. longrifle, the 285 gr. Great Plains Bullet. I will put those up against a T/C Maxiball or Maxihunter anytime in the GPR. The Plains Bullet was designed for the 1:60 and 1:66 twist of a longrifle. And by personal experience, I can testify... it will knock over a mature doe in her tracks at 80 yards! No trailing necessary!

As a part of the package, I am cleaning out the ML box, and will include a dozen .490 ball, cleaning and lubed patches, a dozen PA conicals, and yes, a half-dozen Plains bullets. So, for $400.00, you get the following;

-The 50 cal. Lyman Great Plains Rifle, with a jag on the ramrod.

title: For Sale:  To the moron who does not know what a "straw puchase" is
postcontent:
Straw Purchasing

Buying a gun for someone who is prohibited by law from possessing one or for someone who does not want his or her name associated with the transaction is a "straw purchase."

1. An illegal firearm purchase (straw purchase) is a federal crime.

2. An illegal firearm purchase can bring a felony conviction sentence of ten years in jail and a fine of up to $250,000.

3. Buying a gun for someone who can't can cost you your good name and land you in big trouble.

Never buy a gun for someone who is unwilling or unable to do so.

Most sellers are requiring a valid ccw to buy a weapon, which is close as you can get to a background check for a person. I agree that people are charging high prices but please don't confuse this with a straw purchase....
